 in early processing stages (like when we pull away a hand from a flame
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

instinctively
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

).
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
I will discuss different kinds qualia, with different degrees of global
 availability of sensory contents, in chapter 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Kinds-of-Qualia"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Contents can be transparent
\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
See chapter 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Transparency"

\end_inset

 for what Metzinger means with 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

transparency.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 or opaque.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they are all available, while they are experienced or remembered or
 imagined, to our entire consciousness, to all the other processes running
