\begin_layout Standard
For human beings, the concept of Now has a culturally invariant duration
 of maximally three seconds, so there must be biological reasons for that
 -- which nicely fits in with neurophysiological research.
 On the other hand, as Metzinger also points out, a complete physical descriptio
n of the universe would not have to include any notion of Now -- the concept
 merely creates 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

temporal internality
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for organisms, which is a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

highly successful and functionally 
\emph on
adequate
\emph default
 fiction
