 Metzinger calls them 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

levels of phenomenal granularity,
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\begin_inset Foot
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Nomenclature by
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Metzinger2003"

\end_inset

, page 144.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and explains their mereological, hierarchical nesting like this: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

On lower levels of phenomenal granularity different aspects may be bound
