Dennett's Multiple Drafts and Qualia
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dennett's multiple drafts model seems to be a pretty adequate description
 of what happens in the brain, and really is a replacement for cartesian
 theaters.
 It takes the massive distributed parallelism in our brains into account,
 and computational models based on it (or rather, based on the same thoughts
 and paradigms) do live up to what we expect from them -- a great example
 is Watt's research into auditory pathways,
