\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Metzinger makes a quite convincing argument, one that goes deeper and further
 than those of other thinkers.
 On the surface, it is quite similar to Dennett's: The self is merely a
 model that we create.
 However, as I said, he does go further than Dennett.
 Let's see how.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The self being merely a model does make sense from an evolutionary point
 of view.
 As Metzinger points out, such a self model can be a tool, and a weapon
