\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Dennett1991"

\end_inset

, page 430.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To continue to where Dennett's analogy leads us, a program cannot run on
 just any computer.
 At least not with extensive further emulatory work: A program that was
 created for a certain operating system, running on certain hardware, won't
 be able to run on another basis (unless they are explicitly made to be
 compatible).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To get back from our reductio ad absurdum of the analogy to consciousness
 and the fiction of selves: A self relies on a huge lot of representative
 and presentative processes that supply it with data.
 Data about both the environment and the inner state that the body the self
 belongs to currently is situated in.
 It also is 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

programmed
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

