 pathways -- pathways that themselves form the processes that data from
 sensory organs must pass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Splitting the self from the body is thus not easily possible, as the body
 at least partially constitutes the self's current contents, and certainly
 formed the self in the past.
 A computer is incredibly different from a brain, so in order to emulate
 a human brain on one of today's computers, there would probably be more
 emulatory work to be done than actual software transfer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

