\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
An complex mental motor self-simulation, usually prior to embodying it by
 executing those motor behaviours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of course, all those categories can be represented with different kinds
 of relations, relations that would be called “attitude specificator” in
 propositional attitude psychology.
 Those include attending, thinking, willing, fearing, and many others.
 They also have a direction -- the “arrow of attention” points outward (in
 regular perception) or inward (in introspection), from the first-person
