y to be intuitively intentional, it has to be conducted by a system that
 has phenomenal states.
 It has to be a specimen of phenomenal intentionality, and it has to satisfy
 at least Metzinger's perspectivalness and transparency constraints.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The same applies for Dennett's heterophenomenology.
